uilt a strong reputation for his ability to portray a wide range of roles, from the heartwarming 'nation's twin brother' to troubled, complex characters. A graduate of the Seoul Institute of the Arts, he made his transition to television after initial work in theater.\n\nAhn Woo-yeon debuted in 2015 through the web drama Alchemist and the television series Bubblegum. He quickly gained visibility the following year in the hit weekend family drama Five Enough (2016), where he played the kind, supportive youngest son, Kim Tae-min.\n\nHe continued to solidify his presence with a role in the popular romantic comedy Don't Dare to Dream (Jealousy Incarnate) (2016), demonstrating his versatility early on.","name":"An Woo-yeon","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"安友渊","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"KR","iso_639_1":"ko","name":"한국어/조선말","english_name":"Korean","data":{"biography":"","name":"안우연","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"FR","iso_639_1":"fr","name":"Français","english_name":"French","data":{"biography":"Ahn Byeong-ho, mieux connu sous son nom de scène Ahn Woo-yeon, est un acteur sud-coréen. Il a joué dans des séries télévisées telles que Five Enough, Don't Dare to Dream et Strong Girl Bong-soon. Wikipédia","name":"Ahn Woo-yeon","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"HK","iso_639_1":"zh","name":"普通话","english_name":"Mandarin","data":{"biography":"","name":"安宇延","primary":false}}]}},"person_1164931_translations":{"at":1774731924399,"data":{"id":1164931,"translations":[{"iso_3166_1":"US","iso_639_1":"en","name":"English","english_name":"English","data":{"biography":"Megumi Han is a Taiwanese-Japanese actress and voice actress employed by Atomic Monkey. She is the daughter of fellow voice actress Keiko Han.","name":"Megumi Han","primary":false}},{"iso_3166_1":"JP","iso_639_1":"ja","name":"日本語","english_name":"Japanese","data":{"biography":"","name":"潘めぐみ","primary":true}},{"iso_3166_1":"CN",